Release	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-05-03T20:44:05.6703205Z [{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/pulls/563","id":2914235180,"node_id":"PR_kwDOPUU0qc6ts7Ms","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/563","diff_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/563.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/563.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/563","number":563,"state":"closed","locked":false,"title":"Add /stop <UUID> mode to cancel isolated solve/hive sessions (#524)","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## Summary\n\nImplements issue #524 — gives users a way to cancel a specific running `/solve` or `/hive` session from Telegram by sending CTRL+C to it.\n\nThe original PR added a brand-new `/stop` command, but `main` has since gained its own `/stop` command (chat-level pause, #1081). To preserve both behaviours, this PR layers a UUID-aware dispatch in front of the existing `/stop` flow so that:\n\n- `/stop <UUID>` or replying with `/stop` to a message containing a UUID → forwards CTRL+C to the matching isolated session via `$ --stop <uuid>` (link-foundation/start#112).\n- Bare `/stop` (optionally with a free-text reason) → keeps its existing chat-pause behaviour from #1081.\n\nThis mirrors the UUID-resolution pattern already used by `/log` and `/terminal_watch`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/isolation-runner.lib.mjs`** — new `stopIsolatedSession(uuid, verbose)` helper wrapping `\\$ --stop <uuid>`. Works for any isolation backend (screen, tmux, docker) because `$` knows the backend it launched with. Returns `{ success, output, error }`.\n- **`src/telegram-start-stop-command.lib.mjs`**:\n  - new `extractStopSessionId(text, repliedTo)` — pure helper that strips the `/stop` (or `/stop@botname`) prefix, then looks for a UUID first in the argument text and second in the replied-to message's `text`/`caption`.\n  - `bot.command('stop', …)` now detects UUID modes **before** the forwarded/reply rejection that the chat-pause flow uses, because the reply-of-`/stop` mode is intentionally a reply.\n  - Auth model matches `/log`: chat creator in groups; implicit owner in private DMs. Sends an ack message that's then edited with the result.\n- **`src/telegram-bot.mjs`** — help text documents the new `/stop <uuid>` mode.\n- **`tests/test-issue-524-stop-uuid.mjs`** — 25 assertions covering `extractStopSessionId` (argument vs. reply, prefix stripping, lowercasing, edge cases) and the dispatcher (UUID mode bypasses the reply rejection, bare `/stop` does not call `stopIsolatedSession`, group-creator-only auth, old-message gating, success/error formatting).\n- **`.changeset/issue-524-stop-uuid.md`** — patch-level changeset describing the new mode.\n\n## Dependency\n\nRequires the `--stop` flag in the `\\$` CLI: link-foundation/start#112. If the binary is missing, the command surfaces a clear error to the user.\n\n## How to reproduce / verify\n\n1. Install `\\$` from link-foundation/start (with #112 merged).\n2. Start the bot: `npm start` or via the existing scripts.\n3. From Telegram, run `/solve <issue url> --isolation screen`. Note the session UUID echoed in the bot's reply.\n4. Run `/stop <uuid>` — bot should reply with `⏹️ Asking session …` and then edit to `✅ Stop request sent …`.\n5. Alternatively, reply to the original `Executing…` message with `/stop` — same outcome.\n6. Run bare `/stop` — chat-pause flow from #1081 still triggers as before.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `node tests/test-issue-524-stop-uuid.mjs` → 25 passed, 0 failed\n- [x] `node tests/test-issue-1686-log-command.mjs` → 45 passed, 0 failed (regression check on the shared UUID extractor)\n- [x] `npm run lint` → clean\n- [x] `npx prettier --check` on touched files → clean\n- [ ] CI green on `issue-524-6aa38eea`\n\nFixes #524","created_at":"2025-10-14T16:01:18Z","updated_at":"2026-05-03T20:36:30Z","closed_at":"2026-05-03T20:36:30Z","merged_at":"2026-05-03T20:36:30Z","merge_commit_sha":"3fdb15dda6879b0a21e0f23bf9aa08f1b3fdbfa1","assignees":[{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-as