Docker Publish (linux/amd64)	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-05-03T20:50:02.7593455Z               "message": "Merge main branch and add /stop command for issue #524\n\nResolves merge conflicts by combining features from both branches:\n- Merged main branch (version 0.42.3 -> 0.42.4)\n- Preserved /stop command from issue-524 branch\n- Preserved /top and /limits commands from main branch\n- Extracted /stop command to telegram-stop-command.lib.mjs module to maintain file size limits\n- Updated help message to include all commands: /solve, /hive, /stop, /limits\n- Fixed linting issues in new module\n\nChanges:\n- package.json: Bumped version to 0.42.4, used main's package name\n- package-lock.json: Regenerated from main's version\n- src/telegram-bot.mjs: Merged both branches, imported /stop and /top modules\n- src/telegram-stop-command.lib.mjs: New module for /stop command (153 lines)\n\nThe /stop command allows users to forcefully stop running commands by sending CTRL+C to screen sessions, fulfilling issue #524 requirements:\n- Each screen session can be stopped separately\n- Stop all sessions with \\`/stop\\` or specific session with \\`/stop <session-name>\\`\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
