Docker Publish (linux/arm64)	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-05-03T20:48:56.7692498Z               "message": "feat(telegram): add /stop <UUID> mode to cancel isolated sessions (#524)\n\nAdds a UUID-aware dispatch in front of the existing /stop chat-pause flow:\n- `/stop <UUID>` or replying to a message containing a UUID forwards\n  CTRL+C to the matching isolated solve/hive session via\n  `$ --stop <uuid>` (link-foundation/start#112).\n- Bare `/stop` keeps its existing chat-pause behaviour (#1081).\n- Same owner-only authorization model as /log: chat creator in groups,\n  implicit owner in private DMs.\n- New `stopIsolatedSession()` helper in isolation-runner.lib.mjs wraps\n  the `$ --stop` invocation and surfaces success/error to the caller.\n- New `extractStopSessionId()` helper mirrors the /log and\n  /terminal_watch UUID-resolution pattern.\n- Help text updated to document the new mode.\n- Adds tests/test-issue-524-stop-uuid.mjs (25 assertions) covering\n  pure UUID extraction and the dispatcher's behaviour with a stubbed\n  stopIsolatedSession.",
