Docker Publish DinD (linux/arm64)	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-05-03T20:49:37.3465566Z               "message": "Add /stop command to forcefully stop running commands in hive-telegram-bot\n\nImplements issue #524: Button to forcefully stop the command in hive-telegram-bot\n\nFeatures:\n- New /stop command to send CTRL+C to screen sessions\n- Session tracking per chat (keeps last 10 sessions)\n- Stop all sessions with /stop or specific session with /stop <session-name>\n- Automatic session name generation matching start-screen.mjs logic\n- Updated help command with /stop documentation\n- Success/failure reporting for stopped sessions\n\nImplementation details:\n- Tracks active sessions in memory per chat ID\n- Uses screen -X stuff $'\\003' to send CTRL+C to sessions\n- Each screen session started with /solve or /hive is tracked\n- Session names generated from command + GitHub URL (owner-repo-number)\n- Limit of 10 tracked sessions per chat to prevent memory growth\n\nTesting:\n- Created comprehensive test script: experiments/test-stop-command.mjs\n- Tests screen name generation, CTRL+C sending, and session tracking\n- All existing telegram bot tests pass\n\nGenerated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
